author: Kane O'Neill
title: Burlington girl's soccer shut out Essex Monday
text: BURLINGTON, Vt. - Powered by two corner kick goals, the Burlington girl's soccer team blanked Essex on Monday 3-0. Less than 4 minutes into the game, Reeve Flynn would head in a corner to give Burlington a 1-0 lead. Tatum Vachereau would put in the second corner kick goal of the game, before picking up an assist to Noe Musman for the Seahorses' third goal.
